<br>
And this guy was smart enough to write a script where his activities would cease the minute a GM entered the zone. It would automatically put up AFK and just stay like that. That was why my petitions were fruitless. The GM would tell me there was nothing they could do because they couldnt witness anything happening. I complained to a friend of mine a few days later because it was STILL going on and he came in to check it out. Agreed that I was right. He logged on his druid alt and attacked the NPC and trained it to the zone. I was laughing because the gnome was still standing there unable to proceed. <br>
<br>
Anyway, I went to work and when I came home, my friend had petitioned and explained to the GM exactly what was going on. The GM was able to forcefully boot the character and then log on. Soon after it was verified that the gnome was exploiting, but the GM wouldnt give any details or anything beyond that. No idea what happened to the account  probably got banned or something. <br>
<br>
I looked at the merchant. I couldnt figure out what he was doing. I think he was selling dupes, but the most expensive thing I saw was maybe a peridot.<br>
