<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Lots of platinum = macro + high level fletching. The illegal part is the macroing.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I was one of those people who automated everything about the game. Yeah i've quit now, I played a bard and had everything automated including exping. <br>
<br>
The whole fletching thing, wasn't really 'high level fletching'. Using macros you could max fletching in about 90 seconds (200 anyway) <br>
<br>
the majority of platinum was made via illegitimate ways, I personally made around.. five million plat I guess. I wasn't one of the people selling it or anything though.<br>
<br>
The real reason was I trying to make the game fun for myself, I didn't really think that I was detracting from everyone elses fun (which I was).. eventually I realised that I wasn't having fun and I was lessening it for others.. so I quit.<br>
<br>
Oh and for future reference, the fletching thing netted around 4k pp per hour it ran. If you used tinkering + bow/cams you could make around 30,000pp per hour, per character.<br>
<br>
Hope that explains a couple of things.<br>
<br>
p.s. There is no 'hacking'. There are only three ways someone gets your password:<br>
<br>
1) You gave it to them. You got betrayed, if you have been 'hacked' you have about 999/1000 that this is what happened. Trust me.<br>
2) You have a trojan on your computer that is recording your keystrokes.<br>
3) Someone is watching you over your shoulder and working out your password.<br>
<br>
Nothing else happens. There is no brute forcing, or reverse engineering (of passwords anyway). Believe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archmagi2k>ArchMagi2k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 1:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey</span><hr size=1> Didn't they nerf the trade skills prices so that you no longer make pp doing them ?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enoah35>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 779<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 2:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey</span><hr size=1> The only tradeskill I remember that was nerfed was the silver tipped? stuff made by smithing and jewel crafting. The price of the materials needed were about 57 ish and you can sell them for 150ish. Profit of 100pp per go, which was insane.<br>
