Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nilex>nilex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 6:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey</span><hr size=1> Macroing was an issue and gave the game a different economy than most regular players saw. I've been privy to over-the-shoulder conversations with various EQ developers over the past year concerning macroing and various &quot;hack&quot; techniques that existed in game.<br>
<br>
Put it this way, a real life friend of mine netted $16,000 USD selling platinum he had macro'd 24/7 in 3 months time. Some of the more hardcore macroers made very large sums of real money in a years time doing this.<br>
<br>
There were bugs in the game that allowed you to take over another characters toon and move it to a new location (fixed about 4-6 months ago)... you had the ability to move your character below the world, out of a GMs view and still trade with NPCs making macroing very very lucrative.<br>
<br>
The various playersauction platinum sellers would buy platinum at $100/100kpp then resel it for $300-700 depending on the market at the time.<br>
<br>
Some of the various playersauction folk netted 20-30million plat PER day PER server based on these methods.<br>
<br>
There were macros that netted 800plat profit on 2plat invested that lasted ~8 hours before they got nerfed. Most macro's produced 5-10kpp per hour although some earlier ones netted 60-100kpp per hour.<br>
<br>
Multiple that by a few accounts and whoo...<br>
<br>
That friend of mine would buy up accounts on playersauction and macro on them until they got canned... $300-400 out of pocket was nothing for a return of $3-4k USD.<br>
<br>
(He made 16k in 3 months.. the guy who gave him the macro's made 65k in 6 months... the guy who gave him the macros made.. well, a Lot in a years time.)<br>
<br>
Remember, it's just a game. =)<br>
<br>
Silvered long swords, cam'd bows, tea leaves (alive about 8 hours before nerf)... Whee.<br>
<br>
